  "text": "The Mulliken charges on the sodium cation of the O4 … Na + bonds in 3 are predicted [CITATION_1] to be 0.929e for [U]Na + and [2SU]Na + , and 0.919e for [6Me2SU]Na + . Therefore, it is reasonable to expect that Na + is the most favorable site for water binding in these complexes, 3a and 3b. As noted in the Introduction section, Fridgen and co-workers [CITATION_2] in their IRMPD/computation study found that the Li + cation in the BLi + (H 2 O) n = 1,2 (B = uracil, thymine) complexes is coordinated to the O4 atom, and the first two water molecules of these complexes are attached to the lithium cation.",
